Package: CORA
Title: COrrelation-Redundancy-Aware FDR Adjustment with Genomic Applications
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R:
    person("Joanna", "Zyprych-Walczak",
           email = "joanna.zyprych-walczak@up.poznan.pl",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-9465-3851"))
Author: Joanna Zyprych-Walczak [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Joanna Zyprych-Walczak <joanna.zyprych-walczak@up.poznan.pl>
Description: Implements the CORA (COrrelation-Redundancy-Aware) method for
    multiple testing correction that incorporates pairwise correlations
    into the Benjamini-Hochberg FDR control procedure. CORA penalizes
    redundant discoveries by adjusting the rejection threshold based on the
    accumulated absolute correlation of each hypothesis with previously
    rejected hypotheses. The package also provides standalone implementations
    of BH, BY, ABH, and TSBH procedures for comparison. While designed and
    benchmarked on high-throughput genomic data (microarray and RNA-seq),
    CORA is applicable to any multiple testing problem where a correlation
    matrix among test statistics is available.
